{
  "texts": [
    "In 2023 there was a spike in NC/A-O dataset licences.",
    "Among the large collection of datasets we trace, we record the date at which they are released, by cross-referencing their associated GitHub, ArXiv and Hugging Face dates.",
    "We find a striking change in the pattern of licensing restrictions.",
    "As shown in Extended Data Fig. 1, before 2023, no year saw more than one-third of the datasets released as NC/A-O.",
    "However, in 2023, when many of the most popular and diverse datasets were published, the NC/A-O rate is 61%."
  ]
}